annotation.TEXT: And we're back to Wormholes again.
There we go. Now for a room that needs to add "and spikes" to its name (except there's no room, unfortunately).
Oh, god. Yeah, I've gotta go through all that. At least there are checkpoints along the way.
Alright, I'm free!
Whoa. Yep, that lower-left exit led to a new place, alright.
Final? Am I nearly done with the level? It's been 10 minutes, so I was thinking of stopping soon, but if I'm very close to the end, I should just finish this now!
Oh, come on! I was totally on the next screen when the game declared me dead there!
Hmm... Down or left? I'll go left.

That really sucks, because now I'll have to start fresh if I want to play through the level again (I was expecting to have to do that anyway, but then I get teased about the prospect of a "New Game+" here, only for it to turn out to not be possible...)
Yay, even more strings.

Hmm... I just skipped Machine room with that level design flaw (or maybe being allowed to do that was intentional, given this room's name). That goes against how I normally do things. Oh, well. If I end up replaying the level (and I probably will), I'll play Machine room fair and square the second time around.
D'oh! I guess I should hold right there...
Huh. This is interesting...
D'oh! The platform did that thing again.
And now we're in some sort of squiggly room, I guess.
Okay, now first hit this checkpoint, then check out the other paths.
Oh, it's doing the same thing the main game does at the end with the room names!
Ow, my stomach!
Nice music, by the way. I don't believe this track plays at all in the main game.
Invincible gods, eh? Well, I'm no invincible god, but I see some dark black squares on the right that I can stand on...
Ooh, this is convenient! I can replay the level without losing everything I've already collected! Let me just slip past this final crewmate here...
Well, I guess this is the trap room. Good thing I didn't fall in the center hole from above!
Hmm... Going left once added a tiny block here. (Well, this is probably a different room that's made to look almost identical, except for that tiny block.)
Really? I blew it there?
Dang it! Souleye, if you were gonna offer me a warp back to the beginning of the level, why'd you put that little overhang there so that I couldn't avoid the final crew member?!
Ow, my armpit!
That was easy, but now I've gotta deal with more harpsichords...
Ow, my Truant ability! This isn't good...
Good! Sorry about all that silliness back there, folks. Now, let's try to figure out this combination lock here...
I probably shouldn't flip just before entering the harpsichord...
Oh, there's a trinket that I saw before that I think I could've gotten earlier, but I didn't. I'll get it on my next playthrough.
Ow, my neck!
Ow, my coccyx!
Looks like I gotta get the vanishing platforms out of the way in a particular order, and I have to be careful, because if I die, the vanishing platforms respawn.
I have no idea what it means by "leap of suicide", but Viridian seems enthusiastic about it!
Viridian's loafing around...
Ow, my ankle!
Oh, I'd better take manual control here if I want that trinket. Fortunately, I can stand on the bottom of the screen here.
Whoops! That's okay, as I hit the next checkpoint.
Yay, I reached the end!
Well, going this way led to a trinket, but I could've easily reached the trinket from the left path as well.
Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV! Let's resume A New Dimension here...
Also, I've gotta stop stubbing my toes there.
Oh, I remember this room! So, I could've gone down from here to begin with and skipped a bunch of obstacles, but I would've also missed a trinket by doing that.
Haha, whoops!
Huh, the teleporter warped me back up here. So, now where do I go? Back to the Admiral Ackbar room, perhaps? Or, maybe there's an exit in the lower-left...
Looks like I'm going through the last wormhole here.
Wait, SAVE first, then quit.
Okay, please don't glitch this time...
And now I'm playing sloppily again. I really should've hit that upper checkpoint when I first had the chance.
Moved right too soon...
And then I've gotta not flip down into the spikes like an idiot like that.
Yep, there's the "S".
Yay, I finally made it!
Ow, my swollen toes!
Umm... I wonder if this was also supposed to be an automatic room, but I screwed it up... Oh, well. I should be able to complete it normally.
Okay, seriously. I almost made it the first time.
Ow, my ear and ribs!
Oh, those aren't solid tiles. I assumed they were. Okay.
Moved right too late...
Ow, my funny bone!
Since when have I been slacking?
Oh, come on. That wasn't good enough? Do I have to let off the controls for a split-second while I'm in the harpsichord to delay me just enough so that I can land on that platform?
And let's watch the credits roll... Or rather, me teleporting through the credits rooms while checking my map in each one.
Umm... Yeah, I just got myself stuck using that glitch. I think I'm totally trapped here...
Ow, my heels! (Well, at least it's not the stomach this time.)
Ow, my shin!
Whoa, I just saw a ton of teleporters for a split-second there! ...Yes, I definitely had fun with this level!
Yeah, there's nothing stopping me from going this way. I wonder if those dark blocks are truly meant to be invisible...
Ow, my forehead, neck, and knee!
Oh, come on! I wasn't even intentionally trying to do the glitch that time!
Waah!!! Fortunately, you can't get squished to death by moving platforms!
All the paths converge here, as the room name states. However, the positions of the spikes appear to prevent backtracking through this room.

I could still load up my previous save in that room where I'd trapped myself in those gravity flip lines, but that wouldn't help since I've already rescued the other four crewmates... However, if there's a way to somehow backtrack in the level from there, let me know. Otherwise, I'm gonna have to start a fresh game to find everything I missed. To be continued...
D'oh. Looks like the platform likes shoving me onto the next screen. I've got to board it as it's moving away from the right edge of the screen...
But, if I save, quit, and then reload, I should restart from that checkpoint.
The Mayan Adventure.
So, is this where I was supposed to end up after going left twice? Oh, and is this another automatic room? Cool!
Ow, my stomach again! (Viridian's gonna lose his lunch if this keeps up...)
I'm totally trying to do this room the wrong way... (It would be far easier if I just rode on the underside of the lower moving platform to get over there, but whatever.)
Umm... I hope there's enough room to slip by the final crewmate here... It would really suck if I can't.
Umm... Yeah, I figured I could do that. Oops.
Wow, it seems like these rooms are actually getting easier, but I keep screwing up.
Ow, my nostrils!
Yes, finally! Now, I'm not gonna touch that checkpoint right there, and instead, I'll just intentionally suicide to easily return to the previous checkpoint.
Ah, yes. This is where I left off. So, head left twice if I come to a trap, eh?
This "of" probably should be "off".
Alright, now to carefully ride my way to the teleporter...
Nuts, why'd I let go of the right arrow key there?
Argh! That got it, but then I overshot.
And, the path on the right just wraps around (which would've been nice to know sooner), so I'll need to take the upper-left exit.
What the heck?! Why did I respawn up there? That's weird, but I'll take it!
Yes, now before I even think of trying for that trinket, hit the next checkpoint!
